  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: a45f44d85cfa43adb9008cc0ce89fa69, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  CurrentLogLevel: 2
  m_statusReadOnly: 
  _toolName: Update
  _toolPriority: -9999
  _descriptionForPrompt: 'Use this tool only when the user explicitly asks you to
    update yourself or your software.


    Examples of valid phrases include:

    "Update
    yourself"

    "Upgrade yourself"

    "Update your software"

    "Update your
    app"

    "Update your client"

    "Upgrade your software"

    "Upgrade your
    app"


    The request must explicitly refer to you or your software (for example:
    "you", "yourself", or "your app/client/software").


    Examples of invalid
    requests:

    "Update" (with no reference to what should be updated)

    "Upgrade"
    (with no reference to what should be upgraded)

    "Update it" (with a vague
    reference to what should be updated)

    "Upgrade it" (with a vague reference
    to what should be upgraded)


    Do not infer or assume the user wants an update.


    Do
    not use this tool when the user is discussing updates conceptually or referring
    to updating other software.


    Do not confuse this with to-do list tasks about
    updating software, clients, or apps.


    This tool must only be called by itself.
    It must never be combined with other tool requests.


    If the user requests
    an update together with any other action or tool request, do not call this tool
    or any other tools. Instead respond with text explaining that updating can only
    be performed by itself.


    When in doubt, do not use this tool. Instead reply:

    "If
    you want me to update myself, explicitly tell me: Update yourself."


    If
    this tool is used, your response must be exactly:


    "Updating. See you soon!"'
  _jsonPayloadExampleForPrompt: 'The only valid example:

    {

    }'
  _updateToolIndicatorPrefab: {fileID: 1788539787}
  _updateToolIndicatorText: {fileID: 219046819}
  _updateScriptAbsolutePath: /Users/ritsuko/UnityProjects/Ritsuko/UpdateService/UpdateRitsuko.sh
  _updateCountdownSeconds: 5
